class Solution {
    public Node connect(Node root) {
        if (root == null) return null;

        Node curr = root; // current level
        while (curr != null) {
            Node dummy = new Node(0); // dummy head for next level
            Node tail = dummy;

            while (curr != null) {
                if (curr.left != null) {
                    tail.next = curr.left;
                    tail = tail.next;
                }
                if (curr.right != null) {
                    tail.next = curr.right;
                    tail = tail.next;
                }
                curr = curr.next; // move across current level
            }
            curr = dummy.next; // move to next level
        }
        return root;
    }
}


Step 1: Start at Root
curr = 1
Create dummy and tail for the next level.
Traverse level 1:
Node 1 has left child → connect tail.next = 2, move tail = 2.
Node 1 has right child → connect tail.next = 3, move tail = 3.
End of level → dummy.next = 2.
Move curr = 2.

🔹 Step 2: Process Level 2 (Nodes 2 → 3)
curr = 2, dummy reset, tail = dummy.
Node 2:
Left child → connect tail.next = 4, move tail = 4.
Right child → connect tail.next = 5, move tail = 5.
Move curr = 3.
Node 3:
Left child → none.
Right child → connect tail.next = 7, move tail = 7.
End of level → dummy.next = 4.
Move curr = 4.

🔹 Step 3: Process Level 3 (Nodes 4 → 5 → 7)
curr = 4, dummy reset, tail = dummy.
Node 4: no children.
Move curr = 5.
Node 5: no children.
Move curr = 7.
Node 7: no children.
End of level → dummy.next = null.
Move curr = null. Done.

🔹 Final Connections
Level 1: 1 → null
Level 2: 2 → 3 → null
Level 3: 4 → 5 → 7 → null
